cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on designing an accessible and user-friendly platform for crowdsourcing affect labels in videos. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper deals with video data and affective annotations. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper discusses the reliability of different annotation tools and their impact on affect modelling. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper deals with video data and affective annotations, which are relevant to computer vision applications. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses the applicability of modern data-demanding machine learning methods to affective corpora.
